
	CSS:
	cascading style sheet

	use: web page excellent design in easy way
	
	invented by: W3C company. (world wide web consoritum)

	year: 1996(level 1 dec 17)

	CSS created by Hakon Wium Lie and Bert Bos.


	three types of css:
		
	1) inline css   - with in a tag 
	2) internal css - head tag + whole single html program 
	3) external css - head tag + one or more html programs
	
	syntax:

	1) inline:

	<font style="color:red;font-size:19pt"> i am fareeth </font>

	2) internal css:

	<html>
	<head>
		<style type="text/css">
		h1
		{
			size:12px;
			font-color:red;
			font-family:arial;
			border: 2px solid red;
		}
		.var1
		{

		}
		#var2
		{

		}
		tag1 tag2
		{


		}
		tag:hover
		{

		}		
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1> .......</h1>
		<font>
		<div class="var1">
		.............
		.............
		</div>			
		<div id="var2">		
		................
		.................
		</div>
	</body>
	</html>

3) external css:

	fareeth
	{
		.....
		......
	}		
save: filename.css

html program:
============
	<html>
	<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="fareeth.css"></link>

	</head>
	<body>
	<div id="fareeth">

		.............
	</div>
	
	</body>
	</html>
	
	
	

	

	
